Core reusable parser-related functionality moved to classes in ``lib/parser.py``.  Functionality for generating parser-related values moved to relevant classes in ``model`` directory.  Morphological parsers can now be exported and run locally via a Python interface.  Some tests may fail.  More in-depth testing required.

Major changes. The rich_morphemes attribute of morphologies has been split into two new attributes: rich_upper and rich_lower. Parse class introduced in lib/parser.py, instances of which represent the parses returned by a parser. The decombine keyword in phonology save_script now separates unicode combining characters from their base characters in foma scripts. Infeasible to disentangle these changes post hoc. Tests no longer pass as a result of these changes: 8 fails and 1 error.
Changes to lib/parser.py result in phonology tests now passing.
Mac-specific Command.get_process_children() implemented. Also, long compile_message values truncated (used to be automatic...) and phonology compile timeout reduced to 30s.

MorphologicalParser.parse (lib/parser.py) modified: now takes max_candidates argument which determines how many candidates are persisted to the cache (default: 10); persisted candidates are ordered by probability, decreasing; caching all candidates was resulting in prohibitively large caches.
Phonologies now no longer add word boundaries during "apply down" requests (not necessary).
Fixed formatting of comments in `parser.py`.
Word boundaries (i.e., "#") no longer used in morphological parser FST definitions.
FST-based resources now more safely parse foma output files.
Version 2.0.0 (updated copyright date).

Use RDD type for `transform` operator in Java.

This is an improved implementation of the `transform` operator in Java.
The main difference is that this allows all four possible types of
transform functions

1. JavaRDD -> JavaRDD
2. JavaRDD -> JavaPairRDD
3. JavaPairRDD -> JavaPairRDD
4. JavaPairRDD -> JavaRDD

whereas previously only (1) and (3) were possible.

Add warning for @all / @everyone.

* The warning contains a count of the number of people in the stream.
* An error appears if the warning is ignored and the user tries to
  send the message anyway.
* The message cannot be sent until the warning is acknowledged or @all
  / @everyone is removed.
* This only applies to stream messages and not private messages.

Added new stats and test_stats modules that provide an API for running biogeographical statistical methods, as well as a framework for creating new method implementations in the future (this code was moved over from qiimeutils/microbiogeo). Also added two new classes to the util module (DistanceMatrix and MetadataMap) that are used by the stats module. Added accompanying tests to test_util.py.

BUG/ENH: Let write_biom_table fallback to JSON

`write_biom_table` required the availability of H5PY, this has been
changed to depend on an optional parameter that sets whetehr we want a
JSON or an HDF5 formatted BIOM file written to disk.

I've added an extra test for the case where we want to force to write as
a JSON string.

What this means is that QIIME does not require HDF5 and H5PY to be
installed, however if these two are available it will give preference to
HDF5 over JSON.
